    • Method Detail

      • process

        void process(Metro metro,
             int cursor)
        Defines the procedure to execute when this event is activated. This method is usually called when #between(int, int) returned true. See MetroTrack.progressCursor(int, List) for further information. This methods is called as a callback of JACKAudio processing; this method should return as soon as possible. The heavy processing that blocks for longer time than the current setting of JACK's frame rate causes JACK to XRUN.
        Parameters:
        metro - The Metro instance which is the owner of this event.
        cursor - TODO
        from - the value of from when #between(int, int) returns true.
        to - the value of to when #between(int, int) returns true.
        nframes - the current
